<Docs title="Creating Profiles">
  <h1>Creating Profiles</h1>

  <p>
    Profiles assemble agents into deliberation councils with specific constraints,
    tension pairs, and delegation rules.
  </p>

  <h2>Scaffold a Profile</h2>
  <pre><code>aos create profile my-review</code></pre>

  <h2>Profile Structure</h2>
  <pre><code>core/profiles/my-review/
  profile.yaml     # Assembly, constraints, delegation config</code></pre>

  <h2>profile.yaml Schema</h2>
  <pre><code>schema: aos/profile/v1
id: my-review
name: My Review
description: "What this profile is for."

assembly:
  orchestrator: arbiter
  perspectives:
    - agent: catalyst
      required: true
    - agent: sentinel
      required: true
    - agent: provocateur
      required: true
      structural_advantage: speaks-last

delegation:
  default: broadcast
  opening_rounds: 1
  tension_pairs:
    - [catalyst, sentinel]
  bias_limit: 5

constraints:
  time:
    min_minutes: 2
    max_minutes: 10
  budget:
    min: 1.00
    max: 10.00
    currency: USD
  rounds:
    min: 2
    max: 8

input:
  format: brief
  required_sections:
    - heading: "## Situation"
      guidance: "State the facts."
    - heading: "## Key Question"
      guidance: "The question to answer."

output:
  format: memo
  sections:
    - ranked_recommendations
    - agent_stances
    - dissent_and_tensions
    - next_actions</code></pre>

  <h2>Key Concepts</h2>

  <h3>Assembly</h3>
  <p>The orchestrator (always the Arbiter) plus perspective agents. Mark agents as required or optional. The Provocateur typically gets <code>structural_advantage: speaks-last</code>.</p>

  <h3>Constraints</h3>
  <p>Three dimensions with min/max ranges: time (minutes), budget (USD, for metered accounts), and rounds (deliberation exchanges). Maximums are hard ceilings. Minimums ensure sufficient depth.</p>

  <h3>Tension Pairs</h3>
  <p>Pairs of agents with opposing biases. The Arbiter can invoke these for focused debate. Define the pairs that create the most productive conflict for your use case.</p>

  <h3>Bias Limit</h3>
  <p>Maximum ratio of most-addressed to least-addressed agent. Prevents the Arbiter from over-relying on favorite agents. A limit of 5 means no agent can be called more than 5x as often as the least-called agent.</p>
</Docs>
